The prosecution counsel in the matter of Dr Rahman Adedoyin and six other staff of alleged murder of a Master’s degree student of Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, Timothy Adegoke, yesterday moved to amend charges against the defendants after their trial. Chief Judge of Osun, Justice Oyebola Ojo, at the last  sitting had adjourned till yesterday for adoption of final written summon. However, at the commencement of sitting, the prosecution counsel, Fatima Adeshina brought an application before the court to amend the already amended charges for the trial of the seven defendants. All the defence counsels opposed the move.   Herders kill man for knocking down cow in Badagry     Bridging skill gaps in plumbing     5G: Nigeria begins race for 4.4b global subscriptions   Adeshina said, “The application before the court was to further amend the amended charge. It is dated 14th June, 2022 brought pursuant to Section 211 state of Osun criminal code. The enabling law is Section 211 (sub 1). Section 211 sub 1State of Osun ACJN 2018 She said an amendment can be allowed prior to the delivery of  judgement, adding that an application has also been brought to regularise already filed applications. She said allegations of bias against the prosecution by the defendants is misplaced because they are also parties in the matter. Meanwhile, the counsel to Adedoyin, Kehinde Eleja, SAN, told the court that he filed counter-affidavit to oppose the application, noting that It was filed on  June 23. Similarly, counsel to other defendants, Kunle Adegoke, SAN, Rowland Otaru, Ita Okon and others also opposed the application by the prosecution. Justice Ojo adjourned the matter till July 14 to rule on the application.